        <item>
            <title>0.8.0</title>
            <pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 16:26:57 +0200</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>800</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.8.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <sparkle:hardwareRequirements>arm64</sparkle:hardwareRequirements>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>Jarvis 0.8.0</h2>
<p><b>The Hub, redesigned.</b> Your connected apps are now a library of purpose
groups — Chat, Mail, Notes, Work, Sales — each a card you can read at a glance:
what's connected, what's available, what's syncing, what needs you. Click a card
to zoom into the group; connect new sources right there.</p>
<p><b>Meetings moves up.</b> Meeting capture now lives next to "Your world" in the
header — a compact control that shows when Jarvis is listening (with a live
timer), when notes are ready, and when something needs attention. Click it for
the remote control: start or stop listening, your recent meetings, and the full
notes list — now organized by day, with counts, previews, and the transcript one
click deeper.</p>
<p><b>Your day lives in the Hub.</b> The tasks Jarvis infers from your messages
and meetings now appear right below your apps — a short list of what actually
needs you today, as plain to-dos. Open one to see exactly where it came from,
with the evidence quoted from every source it was spotted in. When a task looks
done, Jarvis asks — one click confirms.</p>
<p><b>Quieter and more honest.</b> One attention line in the header now covers
everything — sources, meetings, Claude Code — and clicking it takes you straight
to the fix. Each screen states plainly what stays on your Mac and what uses your
Anthropic key. In-app search is retired: you ask Jarvis through Claude Code, and
that stays as fast and private as before.</p>
]]></description>
